    },
    {
      "id": "IZKj2ymXd-0l2kLWJ-27d",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 22397.56629102786,
      "y": 964.6196345203244,
      "width": 1138.7384033203125,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b5j",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 279596515,
      "version": 53,
      "versionNonce": 1608297997,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779977320201,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1) Users should be able to start, pause, stop, and save their runs and rides.\n    1. The client app will make a POST request to /activities to create a new activity, specifying whether it's a run or a ride.\n    2. The Activity Service will create the activity in the database and return the activity object to the client.\n    3. If the user opts to pause or resume their activity, they'll make a PATCH request \n        to /activities/:activityId with the updated state and the Activity Service will update the activity in the database accordingly.\n    4. When the activity is over, the user will click the \"Save Activity\" button. \n        This will trigger a PATCH request to /activities/:activityId with the state set to \"COMPLETE\".\n    ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1) Users should be able to start, pause, stop, and save their runs and rides.\n    1. The client app will make a POST request to /activities to create a new activity, specifying whether it's a run or a ride.\n    2. The Activity Service will create the activity in the database and return the activity object to the client.\n    3. If the user opts to pause or resume their activity, they'll make a PATCH request \n        to /activities/:activityId with the updated state and the Activity Service will update the activity in the database accordingly.\n    4. When the activity is over, the user will click the \"Save Activity\" button. \n        This will trigger a PATCH request to /activities/:activityId with the state set to \"COMPLETE\".\n    ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "jGK-1a_QiZ-1ZVzAbD5fI",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 22402.982497582307,
      "y": 1199.6663277215582,
      "width": 952.6185913085938,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b5k",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 443636707,
      "version": 54,
      "versionNonce": 1217474989,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779977321159,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2) While running or cycling, users should be able to view activity data, including route, distance, and time.\n        1. The client app will record the user's GPS coordinates at a constant interval, \n        let's say 2 seconds for a bike ride and 5 seconds for a run\n        2. The client app will then send these new coordinates to our /activities/:activityId endpoint.\n        3. The Activity Service will update the Route table in the database for this activity \n            with the new coordinates and the time the coordinates were recorded.\n        4. We will also update the distance field by calculating the distance between \n            the new coordinate and the previous one using the Haversine formula.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2) While running or cycling, users should be able to view activity data, including route, distance, and time.\n        1. The client app will record the user's GPS coordinates at a constant interval, \n        let's say 2 seconds for a bike ride and 5 seconds for a run\n        2. The client app will then send these new coordinates to our /activities/:activityId endpoint.\n        3. The Activity Service will update the Route table in the database for this activity \n            with the new coordinates and the time the coordinates were recorded.\n        4. We will also update the distance field by calculating the distance between \n            the new coordinate and the previous one using the Haversine formula.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "GSNd3lRW9c3nmUO5qpaN0",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 22413.198552329235,
      "y": 1466.3682325552093,
      "width": 1204.4185791015625,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b5l",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1738828259,
      "version": 49,
      "versionNonce": 1907322989,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779977322159,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "3) Users should be able to view details about their own completed activities as well as the activities of their friends.\n    1. User navigates to the activities list page on the app.\n    2. Client makes a GET request to /activities?mode={USER|FRIENDS}&page={page}&pageSize={pageSize} to get the list of activities.\n    3. The list of activities is rendered in the UI and the user clicks on an activity to view details.\n    4. Client makes a GET request to /activities/:activityId to get the full activity details to render on a new details page.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "3) Users should be able to view details about their own completed activities as well as the activities of their friends.\n    1. User navigates to the activities list page on the app.\n    2. Client makes a GET request to /activities?mode={USER|FRIENDS}&page={page}&pageSize={pageSize} to get the list of activities.\n    3. The list of activities is rendered in the UI and the user clicks on an activity to view details.\n    4. Client makes a GET request to /activities/:activityId to get the full activity details to render on a new details page.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "qglcGrKMdqMVdDm_dSbFo",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 23852.516638696048,
      "y": 983.5453819658463,
      "width": 610.959228515625,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b5m",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2035331139,
      "version": 45,
      "versionNonce": 1123050755,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779981150367,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "4. How can we support tracking activities while offline?\n    - we can record activity data locally, directly on the clients device \n       and only sync activity data back to the server\n    - send data to server once a run completes",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "4. How can we support tracking activities while offline?\n    - we can record activity data locally, directly on the clients device \n       and only sync activity data back to the server\n    - send data to server once a run completes",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
